Please note: We have two dogs; one is a senior, and the second is 3 yrs old and full of energy; both are under 30 pounds. The older one is Harley, a miniature pinscher-chihuahua mix. He will bark at you upon your entrance into the house - my private early warning system. He has an issue with his throat and honks like a goose when he gets excited or first wakes up. We are working hard to keep him from disturbing or interrupting our guests, but he is a working breed with a ton of energy. Please keep your fingers to yourself as he sometimes confuses them with chew toys in a playful way. property_address: Entire cabin in Williams, Arizona, United States
listing_description: Cobalt Cabin, a spacious family-friendly chalet, sits on one acre of ponderosa pine forest in Sherwood Forest Estates. Situated at the crossroads of all things popular in northern Arizona it is the best gateway to The Grand Canyon, Sedona, Historic Downtown Williams, Flagstaff, and more! Enjoy the peace and quiet that forest living brings, wake up rested after a nights sleep in our lux beds, soak in our extra large romantic tub, or enjoy a sunset by the fire pit on our large wrap around deck.The spaceKEY HIGHLIGHTS:• One private acre of pristine ponderosa pine forest land located at 7000 feet!• Perfect for family getaways - Large playset and swings, as well as many games and other activities included with the home• One hour drive to the South Rim of the Grand Canyon, a 13 mile long paved road with multiple overlooks, viewing points, and access to a plethora of hiking and nature trails• Less than an hour drive to the beautiful red rocks of Sedona, one of the Spiritual Meccas of the western world. Experience energy vortexes, hiking, golf, art galleries, world-class dining and more!• Ten minute drive to Historic Route 66 and Downtown Williams, Access point for many great restaurants, bars, shops, and the Grand Canyon Railway - a two hour and 15 minute scenic train ride to the south rim of the Grand Canyon• Newly installed STARLINK satellite internet. Fastest in the local area. Perfect for Work from home, streaming, and more (RARE)• Tons of family friendly activities located within 5-15 minutes of the property including The Grand Canyon Deer Farm & Bearizona Wildlife Park• 25 minute drive to downtown Flagstaff home of the Lowell Observatory• Two ski slopes within 30 minutes of the property, plus close proximity to many areas for fishing, biking, and hiking including Sycamore Falls• Layla Premium Mattresses, lux towels and linens and an expansive pillow menu for the best relaxation and to ensure a good night's sleep• Extra large great room with rock fireplace, pool table, and large premium smart TV• Fully stocked Kitchen loaded with extras such as pour-over coffee, Keurig, nuts, and other snacks• Large romantic soaking tub in master bathroom• Propane grill and fire pit located on the large wrap around deck - perfect spot to decompress after a day out exploring with the familyLIVING SPACE:Walk into an extra-large great room featuring a towering A-Frame vaulted ceiling, large stone chimney and fireplace (with firewood included!), pool table, tons of plush couches and chairs, a premium Samsung smart TV, and extra activities for the perfect deep woods getaway including board games, puzzles, card games, video games, and a DVD library.BEDROOMS:One master suite on the main floor hosts a king-size mattress as well as multiple fold-out chairs perfect for a second sleeping arrangement. The master bedroom also features a work desk, 50 inch TV set, and it's own private bathroom with large soaking tub, double mirror vanity, and shower. The second and third bedrooms are located upstairs one featuring a queen mattress with a private workstation with forest views and the other featuring a bunk bed with pull out trundle and a large plush beanbag for extra sleeping arrangements. All bedrooms feature premium Layla mattresses, soft brand new linens, and extra plush towels.KITCHEN:Fully-equipped kitchen is perfect for those who love to entertain and cook, or just want to prepare a quick meal. Brew your morning coffee to perfection with our manual Chemex pour-over style glass coffeemaker or take a quick cup to go with the convenient Keurig machine. Whole beans and Keurig pods are included with each stay. Brand new stainless steel appliances make cooking a breeze while bringing a high-end aesthetic to an open kitchen. Also included is a toaster, Nutribullet blender, Pressure Cooker, Sandwich Maker, Cuisinart utensils, and everything you could possibly need to prepare a full meal.OUTDOOR:Our property is set on one forested acre with over 100 ponderosa pine trees. Please feel free to explore the property by foot. There is a privacy fence out back as well as a wrap-around deck for relaxing outside. A propane fire pit and grill are included as well as outdoor furniture. There is also a playset and swing set for families visiting with children.Other things to noteWATER USAGE:Cobalt Cabin is a rural forest property and is on hauled water. Please be conscientious of your water usage. Bringing in drinking water can help conserve water as well as limiting shower times when possible.INTERNET, STREAMING, AND CELL RECEPTION:We have recently installed STARLINK satellite internet service at the property (Very Rare in the National Forest)! Broadband speeds are the strongest in the area and support work from home, multiple devices steaming video, and other bandwidth hungry tasks.HEATING:All rural homes in this development are heated by propane which is very expensive. We have left multiple electric heaters on the property which run more efficiently as well as a bundle of firewood for each stay (Dry risky season excluded). Please make use of other heating options if and when possible and lower the thermostat temperature when away from the property.EXTRA GUESTS:Guest count must be the same as the reservation. There is an added 25$/night fee for each guest over 4 to cover extra cleaning and amenity usage.
